      </item>
    
      <item>
        <title>Present value</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Value a cash flow payable in time T from now: discount by interest rate.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex; mode=display&quot;&gt;PV = FV * (1+r)^{-T}&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;calculator&quot;&gt;calculator&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;iframe width=&quot;420&quot; height=&quot;120&quot; src=&quot;/Hedge-o-Mat/static/presentv.html&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;

</description>
        <pubDate>Mon, 18 Apr 2016 00:44:01 +0200</pubDate>
        <link>/Hedge-o-Mat/methods/present-value.html</link>
        <guid isPermaLink="true">/Hedge-o-Mat/methods/present-value.html</guid>
        
        
        <category>methods</category>
        
      </item>
    
      <item>
        <title>Future value</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Value of an asset in time T when receiving interest.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex; mode=display&quot;&gt;FV = PV * (1+r)^{T}&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;calculator&quot;&gt;calculator&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;iframe width=&quot;420&quot; height=&quot;120&quot; src=&quot;/Hedge-o-Mat/static/futurev.html&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;

</description>
        <pubDate>Mon, 18 Apr 2016 00:44:01 +0200</pubDate>
        <link>/Hedge-o-Mat/methods/future-value.html</link>
        <guid isPermaLink="true">/Hedge-o-Mat/methods/future-value.html</guid>
        
        
        <category>methods</category>
        
      </item>
    
      <item>
        <title>Sharpe ratio</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;The Sharpe ratio indicates the excess return of a portfolio over its risk
(volatility).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex; mode=display&quot;&gt;\frac{r_P-r_f}{\sigma_P}&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;calculator&quot;&gt;calculator&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;iframe width=&quot;420&quot; height=&quot;120&quot; src=&quot;/Hedge-o-Mat/static/sharpe.html&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;

</description>
        <pubDate>Sun, 17 Apr 2016 00:44:01 +0200</pubDate>
        <link>/Hedge-o-Mat/methods/sharpe-ratio.html</link>
        <guid isPermaLink="true">/Hedge-o-Mat/methods/sharpe-ratio.html</guid>
        
        
        <category>methods</category>
        
      </item>
    
      <item>
        <title>Vega</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Vega is the percentage change of the option’s price relative to an increase of
1% of the volatility.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex; mode=display&quot;&gt;\frac{\partial V}{\partial \sigma} = S \sqrt{T}e^{-qT}N&#39;(d1)&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;p&gt;where &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;N&#39;(x) = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}} e^{-x^2/2}&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(see &lt;a href=&quot;../methods/black-scholes-merton.html&quot;&gt;Black-Scholes-Merton formula&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
        <pubDate>Thu, 31 Mar 2016 00:44:01 +0200</pubDate>
        <link>/Hedge-o-Mat/measure/vega.html</link>
        <guid isPermaLink="true">/Hedge-o-Mat/measure/vega.html</guid>
        
        
        <category>measure</category>
        
      </item>
    
      <item>
        <title>Theta</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Theta reduces an option’s price every day until the expiration date is reached.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex; mode=display&quot;&gt;\frac{\partial V}{\partial S} = -\frac{\sigma S e^{-qT}N&#39;(d1)}{2\sqrt{T}} +
qSN(d1)e^{-qT} - rKe^{-rT}N(d2)&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;p&gt;where &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;N&#39;(x) = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}} e^{-x^2/2}&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(see &lt;a href=&quot;../methods/black-scholes-merton.html&quot;&gt;Black-Scholes-Merton formula&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
        <pubDate>Thu, 31 Mar 2016 00:44:01 +0200</pubDate>
        <link>/Hedge-o-Mat/measure/theta.html</link>
        <guid isPermaLink="true">/Hedge-o-Mat/measure/theta.html</guid>
        
        
        <category>measure</category>
        
      </item>
    
      <item>
        <title>Swap</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Exchange of cash flows from fixed interest for floating interest.
Several types: interest rate swap, currency swap, equity swap, volatility swap,
commodity swap, …&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example of a plain vanilla interest rate swap using bonds:
discount fixed rate cash flows, discount floating rate cash flows and take
difference.
fixed rate=6%,semiannually, floating rates=(5.4%,5.6%,5.8%), 1M notional, every
6 months, for 1.5 years.
&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;B_{fixed} = 30&#39;000 e^{-(0.054*0.5)} + 30&#39;000 e^{-(0.056*1)} + 1&#39;030&#39;000
e^{-(0.058*1.5)} = 1&#39;001&#39;744.42&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;B_{floating} = 1&#39;000&#39;000 * (1 + \frac{0.05}{2}) e^{(-0.054*0.5)} = 997&#39;695.27&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;V_{swap} = (B_{fixed} - B_{floating}) = 4&#39;049.15&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example of currency swap valuation using forwards:
paid rate for USD: 5%, received rate for GBP: 6%
GBPUSD = 1.50, interest rates in USD: 2%, GBP: 4%, time: 2 years, annually paid.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th&gt;Time&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;USD CF&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;GBP CF&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;forward rate&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;$ per
GBP&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Net CF&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;PV of Net CF&lt;/th&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;1&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;7.5&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;6&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;1.47&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;8.82&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;-1.32&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;-1.294&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;2&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;7.5&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;6&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;1.441&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;8.646&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;-1.146&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;-1.101&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;2&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;150&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;100&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;1.441&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;144.1&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;5.9&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;5.669&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td align=&quot;left&quot; colspan=&quot;6&quot;&gt;Total&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;3.274&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Forward rate calculation: &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;F_1 = 1.5 e^{(2{\%}-4{\%})*T)}&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
        <pubDate>Thu, 31 Mar 2016 00:44:01 +0200</pubDate>
        <link>/Hedge-o-Mat/instruments/swap.html</link>
        <guid isPermaLink="true">/Hedge-o-Mat/instruments/swap.html</guid>
        
        
        <category>instruments</category>
        
      </item>
    
      <item>
        <title>Strangle</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Similar to the &lt;a href=&quot;straddle.html&quot;&gt;straddle&lt;/a&gt;, with this
option trading strategy an investor bets on large price move of the underlying.
It is cheaper than a straddle because we buy the put and the call with different
out-of-the-money strikes.&lt;/p&gt;

